/* Establishment of fancy rats */ The History of Fancy Rats

==Establishment of fancy rats== Between the 1840s and 1860s [[Jemmy Shaw]] and Jack Black bred and sold many different colours of [[fancy rat]]s and their work aided in the establishment of them as pets.<ref>[http://www.afrma.org/historyrat.htm Jack Black, Rat Catcher]</ref> The fancy rats proper did not begin until Mary Douglas asked for permission from the [[National Mouse Club]] to bring her pet rats to an exhibition at the [[Aylesbury]] Town Show on October 24, 1901.
